# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Watermark Vault – Caddyfile
#
# The Watermark Vault container runs a single Node/Express server that serves
# BOTH the React frontend (static files) AND all /api/* routes on one port
# (default 5066, set via the PORT env var in docker-compose.yml).
#
# Caddy sits in front of it as a TLS-terminating reverse proxy. All traffic
# — including API calls — is forwarded to that single port.
#
# How to use
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   1. Replace the example domains/IPs with your own.
#   2. Place this Caddyfile wherever Caddy looks for its config
#      (e.g. /etc/caddy/Caddyfile on the host, or mount it into a Caddy
#      container alongside your watermark-vault container).
#   3. Point each domain's DNS A record to the server running Caddy.
#   4. Caddy automatically provisions and renews TLS certs via Let's Encrypt.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── Your main app domain ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Replace with your own domain and the IP:port of the watermark-vault container.
# If Caddy runs on the same host as Docker, use the container's IP (from
# `docker inspect watermark-vault`) or the gateway address.

book.zacmclients.photos {
    reverse_proxy 172.20.20.251:5066
}


# ── Tenant custom domains ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# For each tenant that uses a custom domain, add a block exactly like the one
# above — same container address, same port.
#
# Steps:
#   1. In the Watermark Vault admin UI go to:
#          Platform → Tenants → [tenant row] → 🌐 Domain
#      and enter the hostname (e.g. book.janesphotography.com).
#   2. Ask the tenant to add a DNS A record pointing that hostname to this
#      server's public IP.
#   3. Add a block here (copy the pattern below) and reload Caddy:
#          sudo systemctl reload caddy
#      Caddy will automatically obtain a TLS certificate for the new domain.

# book.janesphotography.com {
#     reverse_proxy 172.20.20.251:5066
# }

# photos.acmestudios.com {
#     reverse_proxy 172.20.20.251:5066
# }


# ── Option B: on-demand TLS (never edit this file again) ─────────────────────
# With on-demand TLS, Caddy automatically provisions certificates for any
# domain that resolves to this server — you never need to restart Caddy when
# adding a new tenant domain.
#
# The `ask` URL calls the Watermark Vault API to check that the incoming domain
# is actually a registered tenant, preventing certificate issuance for
# arbitrary/malicious domains.
#
# To use this approach instead of the named-domain blocks above:
#   1. Remove (or comment out) the named domain blocks.
#   2. Uncomment the two blocks below.
#   3. Reload Caddy.

# {
#     on_demand_tls {
#         ask http://172.20.20.251:5066/api/caddy/verify-domain
#     }
# }

# :443 {
#     tls {
#         on_demand
#     }
#     reverse_proxy 172.20.20.251:5066
# }
